<HEADLINE> Italian Wins World Cup Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, Italy, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Michele Bartoli
finished fourth in the Tour of Lombardy, the 10th and final race
in the series Saturday but won the cycling World Cup hen he
finished fourth in the Tour of Lombardy.
</P>
<P>
Laurent Jalabert of France took the 250-km race from Varese to
Bergamo.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Paolo Lanfranchi was second and his fellow Francesco
Casagrande was third.
</P>
<P>
Bartoli's fourth-place finish earned him 40 points to give him
a total for the season of 280.
</P>
<P>
Denmark's Rolf Sorensen finished second in the overall
standings on 275 points. Italy's Andrea Tafi was third overall on
240 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
