<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chen Lu Wins in Vienna to Qualify for World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- China's Chen Lu won the women's
singles at Karl Schafer Memorial Cup skating event Saturday and
qualified for the 1998 Nagano Winter Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The first seven ladies all qualified for the Games.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Chen, the world champion in 1995 and runner-up
in 1996, led in both short and long programs to take the No. 1
overall.
</P>
<P>
Tonia Kwiatkowski of the United States, despite the same score
in the short program as Chen's, finished second, followed by
Azerbaijan's Yulia Vorobieva.
</P>
<P>
Chen, suffering right-foot injury after last year's world
championships, failed to qualify with a dreadful 25th place in
Zurich earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
But her blank performance in the competition boosted her
confidence for the Olympics next year.
</P>
<P>
"I am look forward to the Nagano Olympics," Chen said after the
win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
