<HEADLINE> Mozambicans Commemorate Late President Samora </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican people have been
marking in various ways the 11th anniversary of the death of
their later President Samora Machel who died on October 19, 1989
in a plane accident near the Mozambique-South African border area
Mbuzini.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the ruling Mozambique Liberation Front
(FRELIMO) today went to Mbuzini with other government officials
and residents from the capital city Maputo to commemorate Samora
and his companions who also died in the accident.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued by the central committee of the FRELIMO on
Friday said Samora and his party died for the interests of the
Mozambican people, adding that their patriotism will be forever
in the memories of the Mozambicans.
</P>
<P>
The communique said it is encouraging that the accident will
be re-investigated so that the truth of the crash would be known
to the public.
</P>
<P>
A meeting on Samora's education thoughts was also held today
in Xinavane, Maputo province in addition to other commemorating
activities.
</P>
<P>
The commemoration will last till tomorrow. 
</P>
