<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 Killed in Flooding in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 18 (Xinhua) -- At least six people were
killed and four others missing today in car accidents and severe
floods across Israel caused by storm slashing the country over
night, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Thunder storms and pouring rains hit the country from Friday
night till this afternoon from the Lake Kinneret (Galilee Sea) in
the north to the southern city of Eilat.
</P>
<P>
Five people were killed in car accidents on flooding roads
throughout the country. In a serious car accident near Ein Gedi
off the shore of the Dead Sea, three people were killed and three
others including two children were rescued, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
One man escaped from a car accident in flood near Arad in the
southern Negev desert, but his two fellows were missing, according
to the radio.
</P>
<P>
A helicopter was dispatched to rescue one man and one woman who
were injured when their car swept off the road broken down in the
floods in the Ein Gedi Natural Reserve.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rain caused severe floods in wadis and canyons in the
West Bank and Negev Desert, posing threats to the life of hikers,
Israel Radio said.
</P>
<P>
One of the hikers was killed in the Nahal Qumeran Canyon, east
to Jerusalem, overnight in flooding. Two others went missing in
storms in the Beit Shean area in the West Bank. And 28 people were
rescued by a helicopter sent to them, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Storms also led to power failure, which, in one case, forced
the Allenby border crossing between Israel and Jordan to be closed
overnight and passengers were transferred to another checkpoint in
the south. 
</P>
</TEXT>
