<HEADLINE> Shanghai Residents Purchase Suburban Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 19 (Xinhua) -- Local consumers in Shanghai,
the most populous and industrial metropolis in China, are
purchasing a growing number of houses and apartments in suburban
areas, according to local experts.
</P>
<P>
In the first two quarters of this year alone, sales of houses
and apartments in the outskirts of the Pudong New Area and the
Xuhui, Minhang and Jiading districts accounted for 85 percent and
75 percent of the municipality's total housing sales.
</P>
<P>
The experts attributed the new trend to the improved
transportation conditions resulting from the completion of
infrastructure such as subways, bridges and other communication
facilities built in recent years, as well as relatively low
housing prices in the area.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, new residential areas in Shanghai feature easy access
to post offices, schools, hospitals, shops and recreational
facilities, as well as an adequate green areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
