<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Further Development of Special Economic Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 19 (Xinhua) -- China will further explore the
role of special economic zones and the Shanghai Pudong New Area in
the development of the country's coastal areas, according to the
strategic plan introduced during the recent 15th Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
The strategy calls for China to continue efforts to restructure
and upgrade its industries and expand reform and opening in
central and western regions, with special economic zones
continuing to play an active role in related efforts.
</P>
<P>
The nation's five national special economic zones -- Shenzhen,
Hainan, Xiamen, Zhuhai and Shantou, the Shanghai Pudong New Area
and other open regions in coastal areas should play a leading role
in introducing suitable mechanisms, upgrading the industrial
structure, deepening reform and promoting further opening up.
</P>
<P>
The export-oriented economic zones enjoy relatively strong
economic and technological operations, advantageous locations and
preferential policies. Their common historical task is to lead
China's economic upsurge and narrow the development gap between
the coastal and inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The demands of the socialist market economy and the integrated
global economy require the special economic zones and the Shanghai
Pudong New Area to accelerate the transformation of government
functions and the establishment of a modern enterprise system.
</P>
<P>
They should undertake further development in order to provide
successful experiences for the other parts of the country. They
should not only improve their competitiveness in the international
market, but should also enhance ties with inland areas in order to
make greater contributions to the nation's overall economic
development.
</P>
<P>
China, a country with vast territory, has a long way to go to
achieve balanced development between coastal and inland
areas. However, further developing coastal areas and gradually
placing development priority on inland areas will ensure the
steady and healthy growth of the whole country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
