<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmers Urged To Embrace Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 19 (Xinhua) -- Farmers should master modern
agricultural means and rely closely on technical progress to
increase agricultural production, according to Senior Chinese
Communist Party official Hu Jintao.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
made the comments during a three-day visit to Tianjin
Municipality.
</P>
<P>
He called on rural party organizations at all levels to study
the guidelines of the recent 15th CPC national party congress and
implement them consicentiously.
</P>
<P>
And in the light of the specific conditions in rural areas,
farmers should strive to resolve practical problems that have
cropped up rural reform, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hu also calls for still greater efforts to train more qualified
rural personnel and use them well and in a proper way. He urged
local agricultural officials to adjust rural structure, focus on
efficiency and use more advanced technology to improve the
structure of farm products.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he encouraged the development of processing and the
marketing of agricultural products and noted that most Chinese
farmers are still preoccupied with simply growing crops.
</P>
<P>
Hu visited the homes of farmers and held talks with local rural
officials. Tianjin Party Secretary and Mayor Zhang Lichang and
other ranking municipal official accompanied him on the visits.
</P>
