<HEADLINE> Improving the Quality of Chinese Citizens (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 19 (Xinhua) -- The Monday edition of the
People's Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial
entitled "Making Efforts to Improve the Quality of the People".
</P>
<P>
The editorial calls for priority to be placed on improving the
overall physical, intelligence and ideological quality of Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
The editorial quotes Jiang Zemin's report to the recent 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China as saying:
"Building socialism with Chinese characteristics requires
extensive efforts to improve the ideological, moral, scientific
and cultural quality of the entire nation in order to foster
successive generations of people who will meet the requirements of
socialist modernization, and who will have high ideals, morality,
culture and discipline."
</P>
<P>
The quality of the people refers to the overall physical,
intelligence and moral levels of the Chinese citizens, in
reforming the nature and society, according to the editorial. It
notes that related efforts will be an important symbol of the
integrated power of the country, as well an important factor in
international competition, and the base for the nation's economic
and social development.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese nation has created a splendid civilization for
mankind despite an extended period of backwardness and
underdevelopment. The present-day quality of Chinese citizens
falls far short of the needs of the current modernization drive
and has severely hampered the nation's economic and social
development, according to the editorial.
</P>
</TEXT>
