<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Kill 100 LTTE Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 19 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Navy on Saturday
destroyed 9 boats of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
and killed 100 rebels at sea in the northeastern part of the
country, a military spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
A fleet of naval boats confronted three clusters of rebel boats
around 9 p.m. local time on Saturday near Pulmodai, Eastern
province. A large number of rebels on board at the time of
confrontation were bound for the north, Spokesman Ink Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in a fighting which lasted five hours, the Navy
was able to destroy nine rebel boats and kill about 100 rebels,
including 30 to 35 Sea Tigers.
</P>
<P>
A naval craft was sunken after two suicide boats rammed into
it. Five of the crew members who managed to jump overboard were
rescued and the other seven were missing, the spokesman said.
Search operation is still going on to locate those missing.
</P>
<P>
Ground troops were guarding the beach to assist possible
survivors and capture the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year-long ethnic war for a
separate state of their own in the north and east of the country.
The Sea Tiger is a naval branch of the LTTE which is very active
in the territorial waters in the north and east.  
</P>
</TEXT>
