<HEADLINE> Foundation Stone for Monument to "Chungshan" Cruiser Laid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 19 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony to mark placement of
the foundation stone for a monument to the "Chungshan" Cruiser, a
warship which Japanese aircraft sunk in the Yangtze River some 60
years ago, was held today in Jinkou in central China's Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
The cruiser was successfully salvaged in Jinkou early this year.
</P>
<P>
The monument, which will be part of a patriotism education
base, is scheduled for completion within six months.
</P>
<P>
The monument will consist of 25 white marble columns
symbolizing the cruiser's 25 years of military service. The
project will also include construction of a platform for viewing
the river and a memorial square.
</P>
<P>
The complex, which will include the monument, an exhibition
hall and a museum housing relics of the warship and pictures
depicting the battle to safeguard Wuhan, will become a patriotism
education base, as well as a cultural and tourism site.
</P>
<P>
The "Chungshan" Cruiser, which was salvaged on January 28, is
currently being restored at the Hubei shipyard.  
</P>
</TEXT>
