<HEADLINE> Le Maosheng Surpasses World Weightlifting Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongman Le Maosheng
surpassed the listed world jerk record in the men's 59 kilogram
class here this evening in the Eighth Chinese National Games
weightlifting competition.
</P>
<P>
Le, 19, jerked 172.5kg to surpass the world record of 170kg set
by Peshalov Nikolai of Bulgaria at the European Championships on
May 3, 1995 in Poland.
</P>
<P>
Shi Zhiyong, 17, snatched 142.5kg to surpass the world record
of 140kg. The old mark was held by Suleymanoglu Hafiz of Turkey
who set the record at the European Championships on May 3, 1995.
</P>
<P>
In the after competition, Lan Shizhang of Guangxi lifted 162.5
kg to surpass the world jerk record in the men's 54kg category.
</P>
<P>
The previous record of 160kg was set by Halil Mutlu of Turkey
in the World Weightlifting Championships in Istanbul on November
18, 1994. 
</P>
