<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Defeats Australia in Hockey Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 19 (Xinhua) -- Germany won its seventh
Champions' Trophy men's hockey title with a 3-2 victory over
Australia in a thrilling final which went into sudden death extra
time in Adelaide on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
German forward Christoph Bechmann scored all three goals for
his side, including the golden goal, when he chipped the ball over
Australian goalie Damon Diletti four minutes into extra time.
</P>
<P>
Australia's goalscorers were Daniel Sproule with a brilliant
reversed stick shot at the end of the first half and Stephen
Davies with a penalty stroke.
</P>
<P>
It was Australia's only loss of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Spain took its first ever medal in the tournament with a 2-1
victory over the Netherlands in the play-off for third place.
</P>
<P>
Traditional men's hockey power Pakistan saved some self respect
when it defeated South Korea 6-2 earlier in a goal feast for its
first win at the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The play-off victory meant Pakistan finished in fifth position
while South Korea, which recorded its only win of the six-nation
tournament against Pakistan in its round meeting, was last.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
