<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China City Sets Up Land Service Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 19 (Xinhua) -- Nanjing, capital of east
China's Jiangsu Province, has set up a service center to oversee
land management and curb wasteful industrial development.
</P>
<P>
The center was set up because agricultural land are being used
for industrial projects while large tracts of available land of
high economic value remains unused.
</P>
<P>
The center has been entrusted by the city to handle 1,070
hectares of urban land and 186.3 hectares of wasteland in the
countryside.
</P>
<P>
China, which has to feed its 1.2 billion population with its
limited farmland, has been taking more stringent measures to
protect its agricultural resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
