<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus Calls For Integrated Tariff in CIS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 19 (Xinhua) -- Belarus President Alexandr
Lukashenko Saturday suggested setting up an integrated tariff
system among the four CIS tariff union members, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In his letter to the leaderships of Russia, Belarus, Kazakhstan
and Kyrgyzstan, Lukashenko also urged to adopt an integrated
foreign trade policy, to set up a customs management system and to
establish a united information space among the four countries.
</P>
<P>
The tariff union committee of the Commonwealth of Independent
States (CIS) had studied some 60 issues concerning the relations
between the four nations, as the first step of the integration
process, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Belarus president also proposed that some measures to
consolidate the CIS be put forward to the heads of organization's
members during the meeting of the tariff union committee on
October 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
