<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Israeli Soldier Killed in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 19 (Xinhua) -- One Israeli soldier was
killed and two others lightly hurt Saturday evening when their
tank was hit by an anti-tank missile fired by Hezbollah gunmen in
South Lebanon, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the incident occurred in the norther eastern
sector of the Israeli-proclaimed South Lebanon Security
Zone. Hezbollah gunmen fired an anti-tank missile which hit
directly the tank and wounded the three soldiers inside, one of
them died from wounds after being evacuated to a hopital in Safed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another Israeli soldier died in Haifa's Ramban
Hospital from the wounds he suffered in South Lebanon two months
ago. He was shot by a comrade from his own unit during an ambush
mission.
</P>
<P>
The latest two deaths brought to 39 the death toll of Israeli
soldiers killed in action in South Lebanon this year. Over 70
other Israeli soldiers have been wounded in the constent fightings
with Hezbollah and other anti-Israeli guerrilla forces in the zone.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, about 50 Hezbollah gunmen have been
killed in fightings with Israeli troops during the same
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
