<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Records Rapid Foreign Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 19 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign trade has grown
by 30 percent annually over the past ten years, according to an
official from the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
The China Foreign Trade Symposium held recently in the north
China port city of Tianjin provided a venue for directors of
provincial economic and trade commissions and entrepreneurs to
exchange views on the development of foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC assistant minister Liu Xiangdong said increased foreign
trade has greatly enhanced the development of the nation's
industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the foreign trade volume topped 289.9 billion US
dollars in 1996, up 80 percent on the 60 billion level for 1986
and four years ahead of the target set for 2000.
</P>
<P>
China currently ranks second in the world in the use of
overseas funds. The 327 billion US dollars in overseas fund and
bank loans used in 1996 included an overseas investment of 177.2
billion and bank loans of 150 billion.
</P>
<P>
The country attracted 22.8 billion US dollars of overseas funds
in contracted volume in the first half of this year, with actual
arrivals standing at 20.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Forty percent of China's coal projects and over 50 percent of
power and petroleum projects have been funded by overseas
capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971019.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coastal Province to Invest More in Port Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 19 (Xinhua) -- Southeast China's coastal
province of Fujian plans to raise nearly 20 billion yuan from home
and abroad in the next 15 years to upgrade handling capacity at
its ports.
</P>
<P>
The province, with a coastline of more than 3,300 kilometers,
has 125 harbors, 22 of which are deepwater ports suitable for six
50,000-ton docks, or 17.7 percent of the country's total. The
ports at Xiamen and Fuzhou rank in the country's top 10.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the province has 138 docks that can handle 200 tons,
and 30 docks exceeding 10,000-ton capacity. The ports handle
nearly 40 million tons of goods a year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
