<HEADLINE> All Hostages Released in NZ Prison Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 19 (Xinhua) -- The stand-off at Paparua
Prison in New Zealand's South Island city of Christchurch is now
over with all hostages released unharmed, TVNZ reported tonight.
</P>
<P>
A group of prison inmates took six prison officers hostage
Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The inmates, some being gang members, were reportedly asking
the authorities to address what they called injustices done to
them.
</P>
<P>
The 26-hour ordeal came to an end tonight after the release of
four remaining officers.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the inmates released two officers, including a female
warden. No one was hurt in the incident, the report said.
</P>
