<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa Tourists Target Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 19 (Xinhua) -- A major publicity campaign on
sightseeing Kenya will open from next week in Johannesburg, the
commercial capital of South Africa, as more and more South
Africans are attracted by Kenya's affordable prices.
</P>
<P>
Damian Sadi of Top Holidays of South Africa, who is leading a
team of 14 travel agents on a familiarization tour of Kenya, said
the media and workshops campaign will aim to create consumer
awareness about the eastern African country as a destination.
</P>
<P>
"Our tourists have, for many years, been holidaying in the
Indian Ocean islands, but pricing has become a major factor and
soon we are going to see many of them coming to Kenya," he was
quoted by today's Sunday Nation newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
The market in South Africa is price-conscious and it seriously
considers factors such as flight schedules and transfers, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said although Kenya and South Africa have almost the same
features in terms of beaches and safaris, his team has been
deeply impressed by the large number of animals in the Maasai
Mara, one of the most famous game parks in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
On the recent violence in Kenya's Coast Province, Sadi said
South Africans have followed the events closely but the situation
now seems to be under control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
