<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Economic, Trade Cooperation Delegation Leaves for US (2) Eds: details added. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese government sent five comprehensive or specialized
purchasing delegations to the US beginning from 1990. This
delegation, the sixth of its kind, will be the largest in terms of
expected contract volume and the sectors involved.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, members of the delegation will attend
receptions hosted by the US-China Business Council and the
National Committee on US-China Relations. The delegation also will
explain policies concerning China's continued reforms and open-up.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Peiyan and Sun Zhenyu will meet with U.S. government
officials and business leaders to exchange views on furthering
Sino-US economic cooperation and trade.
</P>
<P>
Sino-US economic relations have developed rapidly since the two
countries established diplomatic relations in 1979. Chinese
Customs statistics show that Sino-U.S. trade volume rose to 42.84
billion US dollars in 1996 from 2.45 billion US dollars in 1979.
</P>
<P>
The US was China's third largest trade partner in 1979-1995,
and its second largest trade partner in 1996. China became the
fourth largest trade partner of the US in 1996, up from 24th in
1980.
</P>
<P>
China's major exports to the US are such labor-intensive
products as textiles, clothing, shoes, toys, household electric
appliances and travel suitcases. The major U.S. export items to
China are capital-intensive products such as aircraft, power
equipment, machinery, electronic components and parts,
telecommunications facilities and chemicals, as well as farm
produce such as grain and cotton.
</P>
<P>
US investment in China started in 1980, shortly after
diplomatic relations were established. By the end of June 1997,
the number of US-funded projects in China had increased to 23,250
with a total contractual volume of investment of 36.87 billion US
dollars. A total of 15.67 billion US dollars has arrived. The US
is second only to Japan among the biggest foreign investors in
China, excluding Hong Kong and Taiwan regions.
</P>
<P>
The US service trade with China also has grown rapidly too,
with the opening of 10 US bank branches and three U.S. insurance
company offices.
</P>
<P>
The rapid development of Sino-US economic cooperation and trade
has pushed the growth of the economy of both countries and has
played an active role in promoting bilateral relations, becoming a
major stable element and push for the development of bilateral
relations. And further development of Sino-US economic relations
and trade accords with the fundamental interests of the people of
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said that the visit shows the tremendous
potential and good prospect for the mutually beneficial Sino-US
economic cooperation and trade.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the joint efforts made by the business
communities and government departments of both sides, Sino-US
economic and trade cooperation is expected to crown with greater
progress with Jiang's upcoming state visit to the US as a turning
point, they noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
