<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Kill Some 2,000 in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 19 (Xinhua) -- The traffic accidents in
Romania in the first nine months of this year have killed 1,893
people, including 139 children.
</P>
<P>
Another 5,004 people were injured in the 6,479 serious traffic
mishaps, the newspaper "Adevarul" ("Truth") reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 2,845 people were killed in a total of 8,931 traffic
accidents, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Data published last April in the newspaper "Libertatea" shows
that Romania ranked 13th in Europe in the death rate of car
accidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
