<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Bus Companies Exchange Experience </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 19 (Xinhua) -- The First Bus Company
of Guangzhou and the Hong Kong Kowloon Bus Co., Ltd. have been
learning from each other during the past four years to improve
their service, transport sources have said.
</P>
<P>
Four years ago, when the Guangzhou carrier, prepared to adopt
an automatic fare-collection system, the Kowloon firm offered its
assistance.
</P>
<P>
Lie Zhongyuan, Kowloon's general manager, inspected
the Guangzhou operation and confirmed that the automated system
was compatible. He also offered practical tips on the design of
the fare-collection containers and related management system.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou company now has installed the fare-collection
system in all of its buses, which has increased the carrier's
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The Kowloon company in turn followed the advice of its
Guangzhou counterparts to mark stations and prices along the lines
and to make announcements on the buses in English, Mandarin and
the Guangdong dialect.
</P>
<P>
The Kowloon company also followed Guangzhou's lead and formed a
committee of passengers to offer advice on its service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
