<HEADLINE> Kenya Declares All-out War Against Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 19 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan Ministry of Health
has declared an all-out war against cholera which has claimed
about 140 lives in the past three months in western Kenya, the
Sunday Standard today quoted a senior health official as saying.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the fresh supplies of drugs worth nine
million Kenyan Shillings (about 150,000 U.S. Dollars) Saturday in
Kisumu, western Kenya.
</P>
<P>
A team of senior medical officials from Nairobi led by Deputy
Director of Medical Services Peter Gaturuku also arrived at the
town yesterday to work with the local doctors, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
Gaturuku was quoted as saying that drugs will be distributed
to the five affected districts in Nyanza Province and cholera
patients will not be charged at council and government health
centers.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that there is need to improve water supply and
sanitation conditions as sanitary conditions in most towns in the
region have worsened.
</P>
<P>
Health officials have launched public health campaign to
improve hygienic standards in the affected areas, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
