<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Motorola Donation to Project Hope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, October 19 (Xinhua) -- A Motorola donation of 10
million yuan (about 1.2 million US dollars) has been used to open
20 "Project Hope" primary schools and help more than 5,000 rural
children resume their education.
</P>
<P>
Motorola (China) Electronics Ltd., the Chinese headquarters of
the worldwide telecommunications giant, recently completed its
second assistance program in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Motorola was the first foreign-funded joint venture to provide
assistance for rural education in China, especially in poor areas.
</P>
<P>
The company started its assistance program in east China's
Jiangxi Province in 1995.
</P>
<P>
"We now have a deeper understanding of Project Hope and will
continue to provide assistance." according to P. Y. Lai, the
company president who attended a ceremony marking the opening of a
new school building in Xinjiang.
</P>
<P>
The company has also financed programs to train over 300
teachers for 30 Project Hope schools throughout China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
