<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Promote Coffee Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 19 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania Coffee
Board (TCB) plans to mobilize farmers to produce good quality
coffee so as to fetch attractive prices in the world market.
</P>
<P>
The remark was made by TCB acting Managing Director Leslie
Omari at Moshi at the weekend shortly after he returned from a
coffee conference in London, according to a news dispatch from
the northern Tanzanian town.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the conference, "Tanzania serves top
quality coffee cup. Apart from brewing, the three-man Tanzanian
delegation capitalized on the opportunity to disseminate useful
information about our coffee in terms of production and quality."
</P>
<P>
He believed that Tanzania can achieve its coffee production
targets and substantially improve quality coffee production if
farmers adhere to the husbandry of the crop proposed by the TCB
and various government and parastatal institutions.
</P>
<P>
The proposals include seeding production incentive scheme,
education on replanting and general good husbandry through film
shows and promotional film shows for Tanzanian coffee in
international market as well as seeds distribution to farmers in
new coffee planting areas, according to Omari.
</P>
<P>
Omari revealed that the TCB plans an aggressive promotional
drive for the country's coffee in Japan and western Europe.
</P>
