<HEADLINE> Twin Blasts Rock Indian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 19 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and 20
others, including women and children, were injured when two
explosions rocked a central market in northwest New Delhi Saturday
evening, the local press said today.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, the bombs were placed under tables
on which sweetmeats were being sold.
</P>
<P>
The first blast occurred around 7:40 p.m. local time and the
second came off within 10 minutes after that, a little over 100
meters away.
</P>
<P>
The market was crowded and most shoppers were women making
purchases for a local festival when the bombs exploded.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the bombs used in the blast were of a crude
variety and placed in tin containers.
</P>
<P>
A relatively unknown militant outfit, Shaheed Khalsa Force, has
claimed responsibility for the twin blasts.  
</P>
