portfolios, Chatichai has publicly professed to keep Finance
Minister Thanong Bidaya, who took office in June to replace Amnuay
Virawan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Thanong Saturday indicated that he would resign in
protest against the reversal of the petrol and diesel tax hike of
one baht per liter, which was introduced Tuesday but was revoked
three days later by the prime minister under pressure from public
groups, who demanded the prime minister's resignation.
</P>
<P>
Thanong is believed to be among those who stood for the oil tax
hike to increase government revenue and cut back the country's oil
import bills.
</P>
<P>
In the northeastern province of Amnat Charoen, the prime
minister told a thousand-strong rally that the oil tax rise had
made the people suffer and was a wrong decision.  
