<HEADLINE> Three-Nation Summit to Be Held on Nov. 23 in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 19 (Xinhua) -- A one-day three-nation business
summit of Bangladesh, India and Pakistan has been scheduled for
November 23 in Dhaka, sources in Bangladesh' Foreign Ministry said
today.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, Indian Prime Minister
Inder Kumar Gujral and Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif will
attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
The planned summit will bring the private sectors of the three
countries closer and also help strengthen the South Asian
Association of Regional Cooperation (SAARC), the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The summit is aimed at promoting the private sector as apex
chambers of all the three countries would also be present with the
objective of having close interaction between private sectors and
governments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
