<HEADLINE> Jalabert Wins in Lombardy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 18 (Xinhua) -- French rider Laurent Jalabert
claimed the Tour of Lombardy, the 10th and lost round of the World
Cup cycling race after a 250km course between Varese and Bergamo,
Italy on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
However Italy's Michele Bartoli won the 1997 overall World Cup
title after placing fourth on the day.
</P>
<P>
World number one Jalabert beat out three Italians in a sprint
finish to take the race ahead of Paolo Lanfranchi, Francesco
Casagrande and Bartoli.
</P>
<P>
And yet another Italian, Paolo Valoti, came fifth more than a
minute behind in a chasing group.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert initiated the breakaway after two attacks in the final
climb at Gallo, about 30km from the finish.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old winner picked up his second World Cup event two
and a half years after winning the 1995 Milan-San Remo. And just
last week he became world time trial champion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
