<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic Urged to Play in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Croatian President Franjo
Tudjman urged tennis star Goran Ivanisevic to play for his country
in the Davis Cup, according to a report in Sportske Novosti on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic, ranked fourth in the world, has threatened to
boycott a Davis Cup match against Finland in February unless the
head of the Croatian tennis federation, Suad Rizvanbegovic,
resigned.
</P>
<P>
The two men have been quarrelling for months, but the row came
to a head last week when Rizvanbegovic sacked the coach of the
national team, Zeljko Franulovic, whom Ivanisevic backed.
</P>
<P>
"I am on nobody's side, the only thing which is important is
that Croatia fields its best team, namely with Goran Ivanisevic,"
said Tudjman, who is a keen tennis player.
</P>
<P>
He praised Ivanisevic as a sports ambassador for Croatia but
said that he should not have demanded Rizvanbegovic's resignation.
</P>
<P>
"He is our best tennis player but regardless of what he means
to the sport, he shouldn't claim the right to do such a thing,"
Tudjman said. 
</P>
